The paper deals with the sizes of different types of automata used for language recognition, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also involves complexity theory, specifically the arithmetic hierarchy, which suggests a possible fit under computational complexity (cs.CC). Information theory (cs.IT) is also mentioned in the abstract. The paper also involves the study of sets and their intersections, which could fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DS) or logic in computer science (cs.LO).
